Female body. Length 2.1-2.3 mm (n= 9 ). General color as in male. Antennae each with 18 articles; scape simple. Ocelli 3 . Other features of head and thorax as in male. Abdominal segment VI annular, without ventromesal process (
Fig. 6
). Segment VII long, narrowing posteriorly; with elongate and setose mesal process dorsally (
Fig. 7
